description: Computer whiz Dilton is preparing to launch his pet project online; his very own social networking site for Riverdale High! When the tech-challenged Veronica catches wind of this, she schemes to derail his website with help from the king of social networking - Facebook's Mark Zuckerberg! As the two face off to program the superior site, Archie tries to up his geek cred in an attempt to attract female attention now that the girls of Riverdale have declared "geek" the new "hot"!
name: Geek Face-Off

description: The acclaimed team of Ed Brubaker, Marc Andreyko, and Chris Samnee bring you the next chapter in the definitive history of Cap and Bucky's early days. What was Cap and Bucky's first mission together? And what was the tragedy that happened on it that changed everything about who Bucky was?
name: First Blood

description: When night descends on Gotham City, Artemis takes to the streets. Prowling the rooftops and the alleyways for the first time, this teen archer has a choice to make: Will she fight on the side of the angels or follow a darker path?
name: Rabbit Holes

description: Translates Fantastic Four #579-582 and Fantastic Four Annual #32

100 page special!

The Hulk is caught in the heart of a gamma bomb explosion -- and goes insane! Can the Thing and the Human Torch stop him before he levels Las Vegas?

By JM Straczynski and Mike Mckone.

Also: the FF get a new addition to the family: the Inhuman dog Lockjaw!

By Dan Slott and Andrea DiVito.

Plus: Doctor Doom returns in a classic Stan Lee and Jack Kirby tale!

The Thing and the Human Torch face a beserk Hulk in a brutal fight to the finish! Don't miss the mayhem!

By JM Straczynski and Mike Mckone.

Plus: Ben Grimm tries to clean up Yancy Street - but the sinister Maggia has other ideas!

By Dan Slott and Andrea DiVito.

Also: a classic tale from Stan Lee and Jack Kirby! The FF meet Dragon Man!

Mr Fantastic makes a grim decision as the Civil War looms on the horizon - and Doctor Doom strikes with an army of robot killers.

By JM Straczynski and Mike McKone.

Also: classic 1960's action from Stan Lee and Jack Kirby! The Frightful Four attack - with the Thing on their side!

The FF battle Godseye in the Savage Land - but Mr Fantastic is hiding a dark secret from his family!

By Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa and Clay Mann.

Plus: three great Christmas stories, and a classic 1960's FF adventure by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby

100 page anniversary special!

A Civil War chapter!

The FF have been torn apart and Mr Fantastic is alone. He is contacted by a very dangerous young man... who wants to avenge the Hulk!

By Greg Pak and Gary Frank.

Also: Stan Lee is Mr Fantastic?! Jack Kirby is the Thing?! We dare to ask: What if the Marvel Bullpen had become the fantastic four?

Story and art by Jack Kirby.

Plus: the origin story of Marvel's greatest villain! Victor Von Doom finds a mysterious cult in Tibet - and becomes the dreaded Doctor Doom!

By Ed Brubaker and Pablo Raimondi.
Dennis gets slippered for the final time.

The FF challenges Norman Osborn’s power! The Wizard attacks! Mr Fantastic joins an amazing new team, and faces his greatest challenge!

Also: more classic thrills! The Thing is brainwashed, and becomes a weapon of destruction!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Reign: Fantastic Four #5, Fantastic Four #570 and Fantastic Four (vol 1) #68.
